com.avaya.csta.binding

Class ConvertE164ToDialString

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.ConvertE164ToDialString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ConvertE164ToDialString
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Request to convert a list of E.164 numbers to dial strings using the conversion rules for the given switch. Note that if an E.164 number is successfully converted to a dial string, that is NOT an indication that the given E.164 has a corresponding extension on that switch. Properly configured dial plan rules will yield a diallable string for off-switch numbers as well; potentially including ARS, inter-region and international dial codes.

    The ConvertE164ToDialString request has these parameters:

    ConvertE164ToDialString Request Parameters
    switchName Optional Specifies the name of the switch for which the E.164 number should be converted to a dial string. Note that this corresponds to a switch name administered on AE Services OAM, and that a list of switch names can be discovered using a GetLinkStatus request from CallInformationServices. It is highly recommended that a switch name be provided. If a switch name is not provided AES will query each switch dialplan administered in OAM for the first possible conversion rule match and use that switch name to handle the conversion request.
    e164List Required A list of one or more E.164 numbers to be converted to dial strings. If the switch name is not provided, the first entry in the list will be used to find an appropriate switch name. If a switch name is found that switch name will be used for the remaining list entries.

    The requested dial strings are returned in the ConvertE164ToDialStringResponse.

    Negative Acknowledgements:

    • operation:invalidParameterValue - Sent if the switch name does not match an administered switch name on the OAM pages.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
